Contents of https://azure.github.io/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/02-preview-after-preview/:
*   If any type that was introduced in the latest preview is _not_ in the new preview, simply delete the type

    ```


    @added(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    ```

*   If any type was removed in the latest preview but **appears** in the new preview, remove the decorator

    ```


    @removed(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    ```

*   Similarly, if there is any change from the latest preview that does not apply to the new preview version, reverse the decorator.

    ```


    @renamedFrom(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`, "oldProp")

    ```

    ```


    @typeChangedFrom(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`, string)

    ```

    ```


    @madeOptional(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    ```

    ```


    @madeRequired(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    ```

*   If a property uses the `@removed`/`@added`/`@renamedFrom` pattern to change decoration or a default value in the latest preview (see [Adding Decoration to an Existing Type](/typespec-azure/docs/howtos/versioning/06-evolving-apis/#adding-decoration-to-an-existing-type)), reverse the pattern by removing both the old and new properties and restoring the original property. For example, if a property added a default value in preview:

    ```


    @removed(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    @renamedFrom(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`, "level")

    @added(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    ```

    Here, `level` had a default value of `1` added in the preview. To reverse this, remove both properties (the renamed “old” version and the “new” version with the default) and restore the original property without the default.

*   If an operation uses the `@removed`/`@added`/`@renamedFrom` pattern to convert from synchronous to asynchronous in the latest preview, reverse the pattern by removing both operations and restoring the original synchronous operation. For example (ARM):

    ```


    @removed(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    @renamedFrom(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`, "createOrUpdate")

    createOrUpdateV1isArmResourceCreateOrReplaceSync<Employee>;

    @added(Versions.`2026-01-01-preview`)

    createOrUpdateisArmResourceCreateOrReplaceAsync<Employee>;

    createOrUpdateisArmResourceCreateOrReplaceSync<Employee>;

    ```

    Similarly for data-plane:

